Data Analyst		United States Soccer Federation		Chicago, IL, US		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><strong>Listing Info<br /><br /></strong><strong>JOB TITLE:                 Data Analyst</strong>    <br />LOCATION:                 Chicago, IL                  <br /><br />DEPARTMENT:           Analytics                     <br /><br /><strong>REPORTING TO:         </strong>Manager, Analytics and Research        <br /><br /> <br /><br /><strong>Brief Summary<br /><br /></strong>The Data Analyst is responsible for aggregating and managing all data related to the commercial growth of U.S. Soccer. The Analyst will work closely with the Events, Marketing, and Fan Services departments to receive data, run analyses, and provide insights to accelerate the growth of the number of fans and revenue.<br /><br /> <br /><br /><strong>Primary Duties<br /><br /></strong>This position has a particular focus on event-related data sources, including ticket buyers, Supporters Club members, merchandise sales, and survey collection. The Analyst will ensure that all data is accounted for and properly transferred to the correct destinations, such as the U.S. Soccer data warehouse, CRM, or smaller databases, as well as extracted for future use. Additionally, the Data Analyst will be relied upon to analyze these and other data sources for the purposes of creating targeted sales campaigns and providing insights to other decision-makers.<br /><br /><strong>  Requirements/Characteristics<br /><br /></strong>Bachelor’s degree in Business, Statistics, Economics, or another quantitative field is required. Candidates with MBA or Advanced degree in quantitative field are encouraged to apply.<br /><br /> <br /><ul><li>Minimum two (2) years of experience working in a data-driven/analytical capacity</li> <li>Excellent analytical and verbal communication skills – the ability to convey the ‘story’ from the data is as important as the analysis</li> <li>Broad proficiency within Excel (VBA, macros, formulas, etc.)</li> <li>Practical experience with Tableau or another popular visualization software</li> <li>Fundamental awareness of SQL and R programming languages</li> <li>Strong knowledge of the sport and the overall soccer landscape in the U.S.</li> <li>Familiarity with event-related data and operations</li> <li>Ability to prioritize and manage multiple projects simultaneously</li> <li>Experience with Salesforce a plus</li> <br /></ul> <br /> Miscellaneous Comments: <ul><li>Full-time position, minimum 40 hours/week</li> <li>Some travel required</li></ul></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">As the governing body of soccer in all its forms in the United States, U.S. Soccer has played an integral part in charting the course for the sport in the USA for over 100 years. In that time, the Federation’s mission statement has been very simple and very clear: to make soccer, in all its forms, a preeminent sport in the United States and to continue the development of soccer at all recreational and competitive levels.</div>